`advanced-apps.spec.ts` failed here (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/10857/overview/eb328663-c525-490c-a021-178236bc80bb/replay?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1717606228704.2036&att=1). It tries to create an app but the name of the app already exists. Is this a test concurrency issue? But the test seems to already using a random name :thinking_rotating:
cc @Weiming Wu
That's very strange - the test should only try to make uuid names
maybe it's because my sandbox is broken. I'll try to rebuild the sandbox

`advanced-apps` also failed in my CI run https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/10861/overview/b989be70-1a19-4dd8-acac-9523d3284f52/replay?att=3&roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1

and my sandbox was re-created today
it seems to expect `0.1.0` to be the latest version, but `0.3.0` is the actual latest version

That's also weird because the test is supposed to:
1. create a new app each time
2. create one new version on that new app
3. delete the app on cleanup
